    <string name="dl_size_used_extra" translatable="false">Extra imports: %s used</string>
    <string name="dl_storage_tooltip" translatable="false">Internal Downloads are saved in the app’s private storage and aren’t accessible without root. \n\nExternal Downloads are saved to your device’s external storage (e.g., /sdcard or micro SD cards) and can be accessed or edited directly with a file explorer. For the External Downloads folder, we recommend choosing an empty folder specifically for song downloads, as OuterTune may modify or delete files in that folder. \n\nExtra Import folders are read-only and used for loading additional songs. OuterTune will never change or delete files in these folders. You can select these folders in the advanced section. \n\nWhen you clear downloads, only internal songs are deleted. External Downloads and Extra Import songs must be removed manually, either through the song’s menu or manually via a file explorer. \n\nRescan download folders: Song downloads in the External Downloads and Extra Imports folders are NOT updated automatically. If you manually add, remove, or change files using a file explorer, you may need to rescan the download folders to update the app’s database. This option is available in the advanced section.</string>
